speech.p:
asked the Minister of Transport (1) whether he will make it clear that the weight of the producer-gas equipment mounted on a goods vehicle is not included in the unladen weight of the vehicle for the purpose of determining the class for speed-limit to which the vehicle belongs;

{2) whether a public-service vehicle which takes advantage of the recent order permitting the use of a trailer to carry producer-gas equipment will thereby have

its maximum speed-limit reduced from 30 miles per hour; and will a goods vehicle, equally drawing a trailer for carrying producer-gas equipment, only be allowed a maximum speed-limit of 30 miles per hour?
